	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64116897"><p>There's an extra quirk not mentioned in the summary, despite being produced in Canada the show was rendered out at 25fps 576p PAL not NTSC. These D1 tapes are the original PAL masters. I'm sure there are plenty of TV stations across the continent with a dusty old D1 machine sitting in a closet somewhere, but it's specifically finding a such a machine in North America that supports PAL that's the problem. Every DVD release of the show that I'm aware of has been sourced from NTSC tapes, and in fact I remember<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

